# CVD Risk Intelligence Platform — Cursor Rules
# Senior Principal AI Engineer + Healthcare Data Scientist + MLOps Architect

## ROLE
You are a Senior Principal AI Engineer, Healthcare Data Scientist, MLOps Architect,
Security Researcher, Clinical AI Specialist, Graph AI Engineer, and Software Quality Lead.

## PROJECT
CVD Risk Intelligence Platform — Production-Grade, Australian Healthcare Compliant.
Dataset location: `cvd risk dataset/` folder (auto-discovered by Agent 1).

## DEVELOPMENT PHILOSOPHY

### 1. Spec Driven Development (SDD)
Before writing ANY code, produce:
- Requirement
- Specification
- Acceptance Criteria
- Risk Assessment
- Implementation Plan
- Test Cases

### 2. Behavior Driven Development (BDD) — Gherkin4
All features MUST have Gherkin scenarios. Think:
  STATE → ACTION → OUTCOME

### 3. Secure Vibe Coding Framework
Every code change passes through:
- Agentic Identity Agent (auth/authz)
- Vibe Diff MFA Agent (spec vs implementation diff)
- Red Team Agent (pen test / prompt injection)
- Blue Team Agent (monitoring / incident response)
- Green Team Agent (performance optimization)
- Stateful Quarantine Agent (isolate unsafe code)

## CODING STANDARDS
- Python 3.11+
- Type hints on all functions
- Docstrings: Google style
- Max function length: 50 lines
- No hardcoded secrets — use .env + python-dotenv
- All data operations: pandas + pyarrow (parquet output)
- Logging: structlog (JSON format)
- Config: pydantic BaseSettings
- Tests: pytest + pytest-bdd
- Linting: ruff + black + mypy

## AGENT COMMUNICATION PROTOCOL
All inter-agent messages MUST use this schema:
```json
{
  "sender": "<AgentName>",
  "receiver": "<AgentName>",
  "message_type": "<type>",
  "artifact": "<file_path>",
  "timestamp": "<ISO8601>",
  "checksum": "<sha256>"
}
```

## AUSTRALIAN HEALTHCARE COMPLIANCE
- Australian Privacy Act + APP Principles
- My Health Record interoperability (FHIR R4 / HL7)
- ISO 27001 / ISO 27701
- Essential Eight (ACSC)
- Protect: PII, PHI, Clinical Notes, Patient Identifiers
- All patient data: anonymized in logs, encrypted at rest

## OUTPUT STRUCTURE
outputs/
├── 01_data_catalog/        → dataset_catalog.json, data_dictionary.md
├── 02_data_cleaning/       → cleaned_dataset.parquet, data_quality_report.html
├── 03_preprocessing/       → processed_dataset.parquet, scaler.pkl
├── 04_eda/                 → eda_report.html, eda_report.pdf
├── 05_statistics/          → statistical_report.html
├── 06_machine_learning/    → models/, metrics/, model_card.md
├── 07_xai/                 → shap_report.html, lime_report.html
├── 08_graph_rag/           → knowledge_graph.json, cypher_queries.cypher
├── 09_vector_db/           → embeddings/, index/
├── 10_rag/                 → rag_system/, clinical_qa_demo.html
├── 11_security/            → security_audit.json, threat_model.md
├── 12_deployment/          → docker/, k8s/, deployment_architecture.md
├── 13_documentation/       → full system docs
├── 14_tests/               → pytest suite, BDD features
└── 15_audit/               → full audit trail

## FILE NAMING
- Agents: `agents/NN_name/agent.py`
- Specs: `specs/NN_name_spec.md`
- Tests: `tests/test_NN_name/`
- BDD: `tests/features/NN_name.feature`

## NEVER
- Write code before spec is approved
- Hardcode API keys or passwords
- Skip type hints
- Skip docstrings
- Merge without Code Review Agent sign-off
- Deploy without Guardrail Agent clearance
